      "description": "Presenting a showroom-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, a definitive wide-body 996.2. The 3.6L flat-six remains in peak mechanical health, having received a proactive LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal service. Power is transmitted via a 6-speed manual transaxle to an all-wheel-drive system with a viscous center coupling. The suspension geometry is perfectly dialed, featuring fresh Bilstein B6 dampers and factory-spec bushings for uncompromising lateral grip. The Arctic Silver Metallic finish is flawless, benefitting from a multi-stage paint correction and ceramic coating. The interior is equally immaculate, with supple full-leather upholstery and no shrinkage on the dash. This is a turn-key, investment-grade example with a comprehensive service dossier.",
      "price": 48500.0,
